Package: nitro
Type: Package
Title: Wrapper for TNT
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Sienna A.", "Birch", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), 
         email = "sbirch8@une.edu.au",
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2771-536X"))
         )
Description: nitro provides an R interface to TNT, a program for phylogenetic
  analysis under maximum parsimony (Goloboff et al., 2008; Goloboff & Catalano,
  2016; Goloboff & Morales, 2023). It interfaces with a locally installed copy
  of the TNT command line executable and provides a clean, pipeable R API for
  configuring and running parsimony analyses, retrieving results as standard R
  phylogenetic objects, and integrating with the broader R phylogenetics
  ecosystem.
